## Verdict: **conditional** (not safe to accept as-is; fixable with a small cleanup pass)

I reviewed the seven files, their diffs against `main`, the umbrella mission `docs/definitions/og-dolt-heresy-completion-2026-07-08.md`, and the relevant code paths (`internal/proxy/route_resolver.go`, `internal/proxy/lineage_route_resolver.go`, `internal/computerversion/dolt_promotion_adapter.go`, `internal/platform/objectgraph_store.go`, `internal/objectgraph/dolt_store.go`, `internal/vmctl/client.go`, `internal/server/server.go`).

The **substantive alignment** with the 2026-07-08 umbrella is correct:
- The Dolt two-store taxonomy, promotion-on-embedded-store, and `DoltPromotionAdapter` tag-only interim status are stated accurately in `docs/current-architecture.md`, `docs/computer-ontology.md`, and `docs/agent-product-doctrine.md`.
- H031 / route-over-ComputerVersion is correctly described as violated by the hard-coded `vmctl.UniversalWirePlatformOwnerID/DesktopID` fallback in the proxy.
- `Universal Wire` product references are updated to `World Wire` in current text, while historical filenames (`choir-universal-wire-style...`, `mission-universal-wire-style...`) and superseded docs are preserved and labeled.
- The Definition era is referenced in `docs/agent-product-doctrine.md`, `docs/README.md`, and `AGENTS.md`.

However, **broken archive links and stale superseded-mission references in `README.md` and `docs/choir-doctrine.md`** make the update unsafe as a clean authority source.

