## Important issues

- `docs/current-architecture.md` still includes a direct link to `mission-og-dolt-heresy-hard-cutover-v0.md` while also correctly naming the umbrella as current authority <ref_snippet file="/Users/wiz/go-choir/docs/current-architecture.md" lines="7-11" />. The wording “superseded source material” is accurate, but for authority hygiene it would be better to route readers through the umbrella and mention the old doc only as unlinked historical provenance.

- `docs/choir-doctrine.md` is dated “Canonical doctrine … as of 2026-07-07” despite containing the 2026-07-08 H031 update. Update the date to 2026-07-08 to avoid mismatch.

- `README.md` opens with “self-improving mainframe” <ref_snippet file="/Users/wiz/go-choir/README.md" lines="3-16" />. Doctrine now treats this as historical shorthand and prefers “human-improving, machine-compounding mainframe” <ref_snippet file="/Users/wiz/go-choir/docs/choir-doctrine.md" lines="61-68" />. Add a caveat or align the phrasing.

